Recommends: policykit-1 | kde-cli-tools
Description: dual-mode file toggler for quickly enabling/disabling files
 filetoggler is a dual-mode (GUI/CLI) application for quickly enabling
 and disabling files by moving them to a disabled directory.
 .
 Features:
  * Dual mode: GUI (wxWidgets) when no file arguments, CLI otherwise
  * Auto-detect TTY: Forces GUI mode when not running in a terminal
  * Flexible disabled file storage with custom directory, prefix, suffix
  * Bash completion for options, filenames, and disabled file names
  * GUI with directory tree, sortable file list, multi-selection
  * Keyboard shortcuts and automatic sudo elevation on permission errors
